Nevertheless, the style and narrative character of the sentence makes it probable that it comes from a lost part of the Histories or Annals: ‘ And so they were slain, leaving behind in their sons an epitaph on their departed virtues‚’ is not too harsh a phrase nor too sarcastic a sentiment to have occurred in either.
